        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-09-14T20:28:50Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Protection Against Gouging Activities Act - Amends the federal criminal code to prohibit price gouging during a period of national emergency. Defines: (1) &quot;price gouging&quot; as selling or renting any product, service, dwelling, or facility at a price that grossly exceeds the average price at which it was obtainable in the same area during the 30-day period immediately proceeding the national emergency, where the increase is not attributable to any reasonable attendant business risk resulting from the emergency or is not consistent with market trends; and (2) &quot;period of national emergency&quot; as the 90 days immediately following the declaration of an emergency or major disaster. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
